    "summary": "titleChanged flag threaded across ~70 lines just to trigger onUpdate in an else-if at line 824. The block's own comment says downstream onUpdate has a coalescing latch + throttle, so calling session.onUpdate?.(session) directly right after `entry.name = updTitle` (line 771) does the same job — the extra call in the completed/failed paths is explicitly harmless — and deletes both the flag and the trailing else-if branch.",
